   {:e #blake3 "cecc8a3e072f5d79e6540293e39ebaaa965b9d40d9559e475ebf31545e907f0a" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Innate concepts (components, dependencies, invariants, patterns, anomalies) are a priori ontology that collapses under model2vec embeddings. 4 dogfood runs proved this: all concepts converge to jaccard 0.90-1.00 regardless of threshold.\n\nAPPROACH: In crates/braid/src/commands/init.rs, find the block that calls innate_concept_datoms_typed (~line 295). Make it CONDITIONAL on a policy flag. The default policy has no innate concepts. Steps:\n\n1. In init.rs, wrap the innate concept block in: if braid_kernel::config::get_config(store, 'policy.innate-concepts') != Some('false') — WAIT, wrong direction. The DEFAULT should be OFF. So: only seed innate concepts if get_config returns Some('true') for 'policy.innate-concepts'. Since a fresh store has no config, this means no innate concepts by default.\n\n2. Keep the INNATE_CONCEPTS constant and innate_concept_datoms functions — they're available for policy manifests that want them. Just don't call them during default init.\n\n3. Update the init output from 'schemas: components | dependencies | ...' to 'concepts: emergent (crystallize after 3+ observations)'.\n\n4. The cold-start UX: when braid status runs on a store with 0 concepts, show: 'concepts: none yet (emerge from observations after harvest)' instead of listing 5 empty innate concepts.\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) braid init on fresh store creates 0 concepts. (B) braid status shows 'concepts: none yet'. (C) After 3+ observations + harvest, concepts crystallize from observation clusters. (D) INNATE_CONCEPTS constant still exists (for opt-in policy). (E) All existing tests pass (they create concepts explicitly, not via init). (F) braid init --with-innate-concepts (or config flag) still seeds them for backward compat.\n\nFILE: crates/braid/src/commands/init.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/status.rs" :op :assert}
